NATION IN BRIEF; 
ALABAMA; 
RACIAL BRAWL ERUPTS INSIDE HIGH SCHOOL 
Racial tensions at a high school in the suburban Birmingham community of 
Adamsville exploded into a brawl between black and white students, leaving the 
principal and a 17-year-old student with minor stab wounds, officials said. The 
melee broke out during a morning meeting held to discuss several fights between 
black and white students. Between 75 and 100 people attended the gathering. Six 
students were arrested and later released into the custody of their parents. 
